howtoplay.mcx:debug_stick.header.1=What is the Debug Stick?
howtoplay.mcx:debug_stick.text.1=An item that recreates the one found in Java Edition.\nA tool that allows easy changes to block states.
howtoplay.mcx:debug_stick.header.2-1=Usage Conditions
howtoplay.mcx:debug_stick.text.2-1=To use the Debug Stick,\nCreative Mode and permissions (OP) are required.\n*Permissions can be substituted by enabling Tag Mode.
howtoplay.mcx:debug_stick.header.2-2=How to Use
howtoplay.mcx:debug_stick.text.2-2.action=Hold the Debug Stick, aim at a block, and\n:_input_key.use: Use button to change states.\n:_input_key.attack: Attack button to cycle through states.\n:_input_key.sneak: While sneaking,\nthe above operations work in reverse.
howtoplay.mcx:debug_stick.text.2-2.touch.tap=Hold the Debug Stick, aim at a block, and\ntap to use to change states.\nLong press to cycle through states.\n\n:_input_key.sneak: While sneaking,\nthe above operations work in reverse.
howtoplay.mcx:debug_stick.header.3=Settings Screen
howtoplay.mcx:debug_stick.text.3=Command: /settings:debug_stick
howtoplay.mcx:debug_stick.text.3-1=- Host Platform Setting\n Optimizes Debug Stick behavior for the host platform.
howtoplay.mcx:debug_stick.text.3-2=- Add Unused States\n Makes all states available for use with the Debug Stick.
howtoplay.mcx:debug_stick.text.3-3=- Enable Tag Mode\n When Tag Mode is enabled, it acts as an alternative to permissions.
